definitions.definition: Talk , especially meaningless or unimportant talk.
The vocalisations of a Eurasian magpie , Pica pica .
The vocalisations of various birds or other animals.
An intermittent noise , as from vibration .
examples: Proper brake adjustment will help to reduce the chatter .

definitions.definition: ( uncountable ) In national security, the degree of communication between suspect groups and individuals, used to gauge the degree of expected terrorist activity.
examples: The NSA is concerned about increased chatter between known terror groups.

definitions.definition: ( uncountable ) The situation where a drill or similar tool vibrates and tears the material rather than cutting it cleanly.
